\ id enjlgzgdnjxyjcck
* what kind of things may a type depend on? the more kinds of dependencies a type system provides - the more expressive power it has
* currently (in 2024) industrial languages heavily lack in this regard, despite that providing the ability to depend on compile-time things is very cheap
	* the cause of this is simply that these languages are designed by professional idiots
* depending on
	* concrete types
		* this is "generics" in java and c#
	* type functions
		\ links-to internal eyfagqcuwwajcnmt
	* values
		\ links-to internal vzdcxxawjkqmcakz
* all these type system capabilities are natural, simple and hugely valuable; hence in the future all well-designed programming languages will provide them
